




TY  - JOUR
T1  - Clearance Pricing and Inventory Policies for Retail Chains
AU  - Smith, Stephen A.
AU  - Achabal, Dale D.
Y1  - 1998/03/01
PY  - 1998
DA  - 1998/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.44.3.285
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.44.3.285
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 285
EP  - 300
VL  - 44
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Clearance pricing and end of season inventory management are challenging and important problems in retailing. Sales rates depend upon price, seasonal effects, and the remaining assortment of items available to customers. There is little time to react to observed sales, and pricing errors result in either loss of potential revenue or excess inventory to be liquidated. This paper develops optimal clearance prices and inventory management policies that take into account the impact of reduced assortment and seasonal changes on sales rates. Versions of these policies have been tested and implemented at three major retail chains and these applications are summarized and discussed.
AB  - Clearance pricing and end of season inventory management are challenging and important problems in retailing. Sales rates depend upon price, seasonal effects, and the remaining assortment of items available to customers. There is little time to react to observed sales, and pricing errors result in either loss of potential revenue or excess inventory to be liquidated. This paper develops optimal clearance prices and inventory management policies that take into account the impact of reduced assortment and seasonal changes on sales rates. Versions of these policies have been tested and implemented at three major retail chains and these applications are summarized and discussed.
